               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;Translation according to [[Broomhead I]]: 57: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a1 That which is vitarkavicāra [in the spiritual] that is the samyaksaṃkalpa on the path. That which is ... [in the spiritual] &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a2 [that is] the samyagvyāya on the path. That which is smṛti in the spiritual that is samyaksmṛti on the path &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a3 By practising feeling there arises mastery thereof. Which way &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a4 arises [from it]. By looking back at the spirit [there] arises mastery [thereof]. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b1 [There] arises mastery thereof. Which way arises ... just that ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 Practising the four smṛtyupasthānas, exactly so. The smṛtyupasthānas must be made by one's self. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b3 The smṛtyupasthānas arouse complete confidence. Just as practising the four smṛtyupasthānas ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b4 Thereupon all things are to be observed atom by atom (i.e. in the finest and greatest detail).&lt;/p&gt;</item>
